游눝 Come to Prague Pride with Amnesty 游눝

We invite everyone who would like to participate in the Prague Pride parade with Amnesty to join us. 
 
This year, we would like to draw attention to the homophobic and transphobic rhetoric of politicians, and attacks on individuals at Pride parades in Poland, Hungary and Slovakia. Unfortunately, this is more of a trend than an exception in these countries. The hateful speeches of some country representatives are very dangerous, as it incites homophobic sentiments in society and legitimizes hatred toward gender and sexual minorities. 
 
! Let's send a message to these countries that we do not agree with their attitude toward the LGBTQIA+ community and that such statements and treatment can't be tolerated!! 

仇 Please fill out this attendance form if you would like to participate in the parade or help us in other ways, (so that we have an overview of how many props will need to be made)

游녯 DRESS CODE: To support the visibility and strength of our message, we want to have a uniform dress code. As we draw attention to violence against the LGBTQIA+ community, we want to visually portray this issue in the parade. Wear white t-shirts or tank tops with one of the homophobic political statements or statistics on violence against the LGBTQIA+ community written on them- We will become "living banners." T-shirts can be torn or splashed with artificial blood. Any type of bottom should be black. For those interested, there will be a chance to wear thematic make-up. 

游늸  MEETING POINT: Meeting between 9:30 - 10:00 on Saturday the 13th of August at the gazebo in the Franciscan Garden in Prague 1 (next to the pavilion where the BOHEMANIA Tribe store is located, exact ADDRESS here: https://goo.gl/maps/DSZVmPocptzxKeyQA). Look for the person in the Amnesty T-shirt with the yellow wristband. We will organize ourselves and put on make-up on the spot. Together we then go to Wenceslas Square where the parade starts. 
 
 WHAT TO BRING: Banners, white T-shirt or tank top 
 

YOU CAN FIND QUOTES FOR BANNER AND T-SHIRT INSPIRATION HERE: https://bit.ly/3Ry8U72
